May is Older Americans Month

Older Americans Month

The Administration for Community Living publishes a yearly profile of older Americans generated from the United States Census Bureau. The available data lives in PDF files or Excel Sheets on the ACL website. The code to obtain the data from the Excel Sheets can be found here.

This shiny application uses some of this data to generate graphs to communicate key ideasthe projected increase of persons 65 plus, where this population resides and the trend of older adults moving out of the Midwest. This Shiny Application was built using the BS4Dashboard Framework.

Find other Shiny Applications developed by Kevin Gilds here.
